                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-11-2015">November 2015</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;">December 2015</span> | <a href="/news-01-2016">January 2016</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<p>Welcome to this installment of site news! This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month, and fancontent for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</p>
<h3 id="toc0"><span>On-Site News</span></h3>
<h4 id="toc1"><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for this month are <a href="/scp-1509">SCP-1509</a> (&quot;The Blade of Rebirth&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioghail" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1302192); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1302192&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Rioghail" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1302192)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioghail" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1302192); return false;">Rioghail</a></span> and <a class="newpage" href="/i-not-i">I ≠ I</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/von-pincier" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1315056); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1315056&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Von Pincier" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1315056)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/von-pincier" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1315056); return false;">Von Pincier</a></span>. One's about a blade that causes wounds with infinite depth, and the other poses the question: how powerful can arbitrary words and simple logic be? Check them out!</li>
<li>The featured articles from last month were <a href="/scp-2049">SCP-2049</a> (&quot;The Interdimensional Weather Station&quot;) by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/insipidparoxysm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1538581); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1538581&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="InsipidParoxysm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1538581)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/insipidparoxysm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1538581); return false;">InsipidParoxysm</a></span> and <a href="/new-kid-on-the-block">New Kid on the Block</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1019930&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Anaxagoras" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1019930)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;">Anaxagoras</a></span>. One's about a weatheralien struggling to keep his station going, and the other is about a man struggling to reconcile the harsh reality around him with his internalized fantasies. Check them out if you missed them!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc2"><span>Rest of the News</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=966960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="anqxyr" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=966960)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anqxyr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(966960); return false;">anqxyr</a></span> has moved his <a href="/ebooks">Ebooks</a> project out of the forums and onto the main site! If you wanna read the site (and even the <a href="http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/">Wanderer's Library</a> too) on the go, this is something to check out.</li>
<li>The Deletions policy has been updated and in effect for the past half-month. You can see the revisions <a href="/deletions-guide">here</a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1449719/4th-annual-scp-holiday-art-exchange">4th Annual SCP Holiday Art Exchange</a> has come and gone, and lots of exciting gifts! From tales, to pictures, to even a tabletop RPG setting! Come see all the wonderful creativity on tap from the community!</li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1379080&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Randomini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1379080)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span> has finished the <a href="/advent-calendar-2015">Randomini Continues Talking Despite The Best Efforts Of Almost Everyone He Knows: Advent Calendar Edition v2015</a>! A link to his Bandcamp, where you can download it and pay what you want, contains all readings and even bonus tracks! Go check it out; it's a great time.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>Missing out on articles? Enjoy a recap on the articles from the past month, as 2016 has rolled in, and we take a look at the final articles of 2015!</p>
<h3 id="toc3"><span>Week of December 1st</span></h3>
<p>In dire need of some entertainment? Go ditch Cousin Johnny, cause we got a show for you.</p>
<h4 id="toc4"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2848">SCP-2848</a> (&quot;Leave It All Behind&quot;) - When fate thrusts you into a life anew as a second chance, it's often to make sure you learn a lesson. Grieving can be hard, but we all must move past it. Originally written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1229263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Roget" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1229263)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1229263); return false;">Roget</a></span>, rewritten by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/troyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(451071); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=451071&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TroyL" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=451071)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/troyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(451071); return false;">TroyL</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3v1l-j">SCP-3V1L-J</a> (&quot;The Master Plan&quot;) - You fool! All along, you had thought this was going to be a joke article about some incompetent villain. But little did you know, everything went all according to plan! I even got my henchman <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2034230&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="daveyoufool" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2034230)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daveyoufool" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2034230); return false;">daveyoufool</a></span> to write up my exploits!</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2430">SCP-2430</a> (&quot;Immortal Hitler Clone&quot;) - When you have acquired pounds of regenerating flesh, what do you do with it? <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Make it a human-shaped</span> - I mean, let justice be served. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/audio-log-from-december-24th-2010">Audio Log From December 24th, 2010</a> - You know, no one's ever tried singing about SCP-055. Do we&#8230; have an SCP-055? Written and sung by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1414765&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Doctor Cimmerian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1414765)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;">Doctor Cimmerian</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/project-morpheus">Project Morpheus</a> - The Foundation uses SCP-990 to go into a person's dreams and utilize them for recon and intelligence. The Oneiroi aren't too pleased about it, however. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/of-dragons-and-serpents">CotBG Archive ██/██/20██-███: Of Dragons and Serpents</a> - Poems about the Broken God in all of their glory. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1621343&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="SunnyClockwork" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1621343)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sunnyclockwork" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1621343); return false;">SunnyClockwork</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/funerals-are-fun">Funerals Are Fun</a> - A funeral held for a beloved gets crashed for a prank TV show. Hilarity ensues! Lots of laughs to be had! Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;">WrongJohnSilver</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc6"><span>GoI Formats</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/grant-request-for-the-construction-of-an-interstellar-scienc">GRANT REQUEST FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF AN INTERSTELLAR SCIENCE VESSEL</a> - Prometheus Labs has always dreamed big, and there's nothing around bigger than space. So the logical conclusion is to build a starship powered by a black hole. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;">GreenWolf</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="toc7"><span>Week of December 8th</span></h3>
<p>Spaaace. SPAAAAAACE. As if the last week didn't have enough space for you, you get even more for this week!</p>
<h4 id="toc8"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-1075">SCP-1075</a> (&quot;The Forest Normally Known as Vince&quot;) - In the cold Colorado mountains, one man is a forest. Or maybe the forest is a man. Honestly I'm not really sure anymore. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1414765&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Doctor Cimmerian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1414765)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;">Doctor Cimmerian</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2484">SCP-2484</a> (&quot;Parasitic Mayonnaise Worms&quot;) - Mayonnaise hasn't ever tasted more disgusting until now. Made with EGGS. LOTS OF EGGS. YOURE BODY IS OUR HOME, and lots of love. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-solo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1476008); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1476008&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Dr Solo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1476008)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-solo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1476008); return false;">Dr Solo</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2511">SCP-2511</a> (&quot;Kappa Population Distribution: More in Mongolia than anywhere else&quot;) - The kappa is more commonly found in Mongolia. They can be found in Japan too, but there are less of them there. That's how things are. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc9"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/database-error">Database error?</a> - A junior researcher has low-level clearance for <a href="/scp-2140">2140</a>, and tries to figure out what purpose it serves while struggling with disturbing dreams. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/hamibombard1">The HAMI-BOMBARD Blues, Part I</a> - &quot;Hey guys, I was thinking, how do we make a giant metal humanoid machine more dangerous?&quot; &quot;You still got them nukes? I bet we could put one on the arm.&quot; Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/von-pincier" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1315056); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1315056&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="Von Pincier" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1315056)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/von-pincier" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1315056); return false;">Von Pincier</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/rip">R.I.P.</a> - Sex, Death, and Rock &amp; Roll. The Cowboy rides again. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=224440&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="AdminBright" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=224440)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;">AdminBright</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/loss-and-nostalgia">Loss and Nostalgia</a> - A series of vignettes connected to tell a tale about, well, loss and nostalgia. Whether you're a space goddess, an artist, or a religious follower, they're all feelings that resonate. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="/a-site-19-christmas-carol">A Site-19 Christmas Carol</a> - 'tis the season to be jolly! Some odd researcher has composed a grand stage play in the style of 'A Christmas Carol' for Foundation employees! But printers are only for work, people. Definitely not written incognito by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc10"><span>GoI Formats</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/grant-request-for-the-development-of-tools-for-mapping-local">GRANT REQUEST FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF TOOLS FOR MAPPING LOCALES WITH INCONSISTENT SPACETIME</a> - Never get lost again with the new Prometheus Labs Spacetime Mapping Unit! Capable of navigating even the most severe anomalies, this is an essential tool for any anomologist or extradimensional explorer. Written by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ajmansfield" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2238949); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2238949&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="AJMansfield" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2238949)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ajmansfield" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2238949); return false;">AJMansfield</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc11"><span>Author Pages</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/ajmansfield">AJMansfield's Author Page</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ajmansfield" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2238949); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2238949&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869486" alt="AJMansfield" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2238949)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ajmansfield" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2238949); return false;">AJMansfield</a></span>'s author page! Pretty concise, isn't it? You got the articles listed, any <a href="http://sandbox.scp-wiki.net/achievement-badges">arbitrary awards</a>, and their ratings. Wholly effective.</li>
</ul>
